    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-18T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-18T02:00:00-05:00" n="906"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d906">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">894.6363/203: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-18T16:00:00+09:00"
                            >July 18, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 18—5:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>152. Department’s 110, July 17, 4 p.m., petroleum regulations in Japan. The
                    Minister for Foreign Affairs told me this morning that <pb facs="1035" n="923"
                        xml:id="pg_923"/> the matter has been discussed in Cabinet and is now under
                    consideration of Ministers of Commerce, Finance, War, Navy and Foreign Affairs.
                    He did not predict the outcome.</p>
                <p>Kurusu states that he is encountering opposition by some of the Ministries to the
                    desired modification of the law but he hopes to obtain before October 1st a
                    satisfactory settlement by discreet use of the compelling argument that Japan is
                    dependent on foreign oil.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
